# AI Resume Analyser Architecture & Flows

Here are the comprehensive Mermaid diagrams illustrating the architecture, system flow, and database schema for the **AI Resume Analyser** project. 

## 1. High-Level Architecture
This logical architecture diagram shows how the frontend interacts with the Spring Boot backend, traversing through controllers, services, repositories, and ultimately connecting to the database and the OpenAI API.

```mermaid
graph TD
  %% Styling configuration for premium look
  classDef user fill:#ffecb3,stroke:#ffb300,stroke-width:2px,color:#333;
  classDef frontend fill:#bbdefb,stroke:#1e88e5,stroke-width:2px,color:#333,rx:10,ry:10;
  classDef controller fill:#c8e6c9,stroke:#43a047,stroke-width:2px,color:#333,rx:5,ry:5;
  classDef service fill:#ffe0b2,stroke:#fb8c00,stroke-width:2px,color:#333,rx:5,ry:5;
  classDef repository fill:#e1bee7,stroke:#8e24aa,stroke-width:2px,color:#333,rx:5,ry:5;
  classDef database fill:#f8bbd0,stroke:#d81b60,stroke-width:2px,shape:cylinder,color:#333;
  classDef external fill:#cfd8dc,stroke:#546e7a,stroke-width:2px,stroke-dasharray: 5 5,color:#333;

  %% Actors
  User((User)):::user
  UI["Frontend Client<br/>(Browser)"]:::frontend

  %% Layer 1: Presentation
  subgraph Presentation Layer
    AuthController["AuthController<br/>REST API (/api/auth)"]:::controller
    ResumeController["ResumeController<br/>REST API (/api/resume)"]:::controller
  end

  %% Layer 2: Business Logic
  subgraph Business Logic Layer
    ResumeAnalysisService["ResumeAnalysisService<br/>Manages Analysis Workflow"]:::service
    FileParserService["FileParserService<br/>(Apache PDFBox / POI)"]:::service
    OpenAIService["OpenAIService<br/>OkHttp LLM Integration"]:::service
  end

  %% Layer 3: Data Access
  subgraph Data Access Layer
    UserRepository["UserRepository<br/>(Spring Data JPA)"]:::repository
    ResumeAnalysisRepository["ResumeAnalysisRepository<br/>(Spring Data JPA)"]:::repository
  end

  %% Infrastructure
  DB[("MySQL / H2 DB")]:::database
  LLM["OpenAI LLM API"]:::external

  %% Core Interactions
  User -->|Login / Upload Document| UI
  
  UI -->|Authenticate| AuthController
  UI -->|Upload Resume / JD| ResumeController
  
  AuthController -->|Find/Save| UserRepository
  UserRepository -->|JPA| DB
  
  ResumeController -->|Parse File| FileParserService
  ResumeController -->|Initiate Analysis| ResumeAnalysisService
  
  ResumeAnalysisService -->|Extract Text| FileParserService
  ResumeAnalysisService -->|Build Prompt & Query| OpenAIService
  OpenAIService -->|HTTP Request| LLM
  LLM -.->|JSON Evaluation| OpenAIService
  OpenAIService -->|Parsed Result| ResumeAnalysisService
  
  ResumeAnalysisService -->|Save Analysis| ResumeAnalysisRepository
  ResumeAnalysisRepository -->|JPA| DB
```

---

## 2. Resume Processing Sequence Diagram
This scenario details the exact sequence of events when a user uploads their resume.

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant UI as Frontend Browser
    participant RC as ResumeController
    participant FS as FileParserService
    participant RS as ResumeAnalysisService
    participant OS as OpenAIService
    participant OAI as OpenAI API
    participant DB as SQL Database

    U->>UI: Uploads Resume (PDF/DOCX) & Appends optional JD
    UI->>RC: POST /api/resume/analyze (MultipartForm)
    RC->>FS: extractText(file)
    FS-->>RC: String (Extracted Resume Text)
    
    RC->>RS: analyzeResume(userId, text, jd, originalFileName)
    RS->>DB: Save "PENDING" Analysis State (Optional)
    
    RS->>OS: callLLMForAnalysis(text, jd)
    OS->>OAI: HTTP POST (Prompt including JD and Text)
    Note over OAI,OS: Analyzing structure, missing skills,<br/>match score & creating summary
    OAI-->>OS: JSON Response (Score, Suggestions)
    
    OS-->>RS: Parsed Analysis Map
    
    RS->>DB: Save processing results into ResumeAnalysis Entity
    DB-->>RS: Analysis Details Saved Successfully
    
    RS-->>RC: Returns 'ResumeAnalysisResponse' DTO
    RC-->>UI: 200 OK + JSON DTO
    UI-->>U: Visualizes Scores, Explanations, and Missing Skills
```

---

## 3. Database Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD)
This diagram models the key objects stored in the `MySQL` / `H2` database and how they relate to the application context.

```mermaid
erDiagram
    %% Entities
    USER {
        bigint id PK
        string username
        string password
        string email
        string role
        datetime createdAt
    }

    RESUME_ANALYSIS {
        bigint id PK
        bigint user_id FK
        string file_name
        string original_file_name
        string file_type
        bigint file_size
        string candidate_name
        string candidate_email 
        int overall_score
        int ats_score
        int skills_score
        int experience_score
        int formatting_score
        int jd_match_score
        text extracted_skills
        text strengths
        text weaknesses
        text suggestions
        text keywords_missing
        longtext raw_text
        string analysis_status
        datetime created_at
        datetime updated_at
    }

    %% Relationships
    USER ||--o{ RESUME_ANALYSIS : "owns / initiates"
```
